originalText.text: I needed spider control in my basement, and the service was exceptional. They eliminated the spiders and offered valuable tips to prevent future infestations. Thanks, Henry, for your thorough work!

originalText.text: Dealing with a persistent cockroach problem in my apartment was frustrating, but the cockroach extermination service worked wonders. My apartment is now free from these unwelcome pests. Thanks a ton, Henry and the team.

originalText.text: The work was great and the technician was very clear on what the issue was and what needed to be done. However, I am confused as to why people are saying this is affordable!!! I had two areas serviced (holes covered mouse traps and poison) and was charged $770. I guess when you just want your issue solved you have no choice but to pay lol overall it's a necessary evil and I can now live rodent free... I hope! update to come after a few months :)

originalText.text: The inspector, Jonathan, who came to give us a quote was friendly, professional, knowledgeable, helpful - all the things you want in someone coming into your home. He didn't try to sell us on anything. He just let us know the best thing to do for our family. I will recommend him to anyone who needs help with pests!

originalText.text: I had a bad roach problem.  The exterminator was arrogant and refused to do a thorough job; ie spreading gel in kitchen drawers etc.  So i gave it one month to see  problem lessen.  In fact at the end of that time i had nany many more roaches than i began with.  For 225$ i think i should be able to expect a lessening of the problem.  The best they could offer me was 25$ off the followup visit.  Mike the owner was not helpful at all and wss arrogant.  Not a way to do business
